    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hard, close-grained, durable wood of the species Quercus stellata, native to sandy soils of the central and southern United States. It is tough and rot-resistant, used for fence posts, rough construction, and as a fuel for barbequing meat.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
